<br>
When you zone in, you're up on a telepad, this is where I'm bound right now.  What you wanna do first is invis up, and run around the forest, there are pansie traps all over the forest, and these lil buggers are mean.  There are only 2 pansies and once you trigger a trap, they pop, and if yer invis, they depop right away so you don't have to kill them.  The repop on the traps is 6 hours.  On the PoM page there's a link to the PoM message board and there are actually a bunch of locs as to where the traps are.  Once the pansie traps are gone, you can move around freely in the forest.  In the forest, you can kill the shrooms and halflings and not take any faction hits.  Most of these are green to lvl 59.  There is 1 treasure chest that's kos but it's permarooted.  Epic pet can tank all these mobs, they hit for like 100 max.  They drop the squire cards and the 4 corners of WoWs.  <br>
<br>
Another good place to solo/duo is the maze.  There are a bunch of rats in there that are all blue to a lvl 60.  They hit for about 120ish.  They don't summon so you can always gate out and camp out aggro if things get bad.  To get to the maze, you'll have to go into the castle.  There is a visible ramp leading up to the castle, but it's a trap.  (you just fall into water)... there is an invisible ramp to the right of the visible ramp and that's how you run up.  There are also dispell traps when you run into the castle but sometimes if you can time it right you don't get dispelled at all.  Once inside the castle entrance, just run forward towards the gate in front of you past the 2 skunk guards.  You will then drop down into the maze.  PoM site has a really good map of the maze (thx sulanja of IV!) and there is a room close to that drop off that I camp in with my wizard buddy.  There is 1 wanderer in there I believe, and that's where we setup camp.  About 20 rats can be pulled to there and then it gets empty.  The rats also drop squire cards and WoW pieces.<br>
<br>
Other than the forest and the rat maze we haven't found another good place to duo.  I'll let you guys know if we find another good spot.  We recently tried the mobs in the garden, but they chew up my epic pet like crazy plus they summon so we had to evac.  I think their max hit is around 200ish.  <br>
<br>
To get the throne cards you'll have to have a very solid group - a tough main tank and cleric and chanter is a must.  They drop often in the alice in wonderland wing and from the puppets.  <br>
<br>
You can wander around PoM freely, there aren't any kos mobs except for &quot;five&quot; I believe, but he's perma rooted and there to scare people since he hits for like 3 dmg or something.  There's also a rabbit and some other dude that's kos (see pom site).  I was able to explore PoM with 2 others pretty freely and nothing attacked us.  <br>
<br>
Be careful with hailing the npcs/mobs there.  Don't ever hail the gorillas!  they will attack you if you hail them.  <br>
<br>
I won't go into the details of the quests and how to make armor pieces, it's all there at the pom website.  There are some pretty sweet things up there <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    I recently just aquired a black flower, it adds like 40DR (recently nerfed to self only <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )  Most of the good things up in PoM (class specific armor), you will need a solid group or a raiding party to do.  Just make sure your cleric is bound in PoM.  If not CR for the melee will be hell since you have to clear most of north ToV to get to PoM!<br>
